<br>
Obviously this is a bad idea from the perspective that bot accounts equate to extra profit, so it's unlikely to happen.  I think it would work though. <p>-Aurra Sing-</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrandynaquilius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brandyn Aquilius</A> at: 7/17/02 5:18:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umelanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melanu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/17/02 6:13:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3766.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A fair change to balance out buff bots.</span><hr size=1> I think we need to keep threads like this going for two reasons.<br>
1.  Hey it's not a bad idea<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I would say 10 min checks is fine.  Especially if they made buffs instant cast.<br>
<br>
2.  If we don't keep this going mythic could easily view us as the problem and not buff bots.<br>
<br>
Mel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unage42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nage42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/17/02 10:21:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3766.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A fair change to balance out buff bots.</span><hr size=1> Heya;<br>
<br>
I think I brought up this topic on my board and it met with broad support (Lihp is on our server and his buffbot is amazing).<br>
<br>
One key aspect that needs to be maintained is that if you buff say a guard of a keep then you need to know when it disapears (guard dies).  This plays a large role in keep defence while roaming around.<br>
<br>
Other than that, the idea of buffs on a range needs to go forward -- not sure how this can get put to the right people, but I suspect that if it was addressed then the outcry for &quot;NERF ASSASSINS&quot; would abate.<br>
<br>
All legitimate assassins out there should keep it in mind that their buffbot handjob using brethren are by their actions motivating the vocal majority of classes out there to get us all nerfed across the board -- something to think about.<br>
<br>
The next step would be to remove the Stun of DragonFang and DiamondBack and make them medium stun 2-step chains at 18 -&gt; 39 (like LeftAxe).  Allow the Infs/NSs their respec where they prolly chose Slash (make Assassin using Slash a Dex-based weapon?).  Infs with Slash are really tough, but at least they are not demigods like Thrust 50 Infs are.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if anyone's got friends in high places, bring up the buffs-on-range topic, get it addressed, but not in a way that hurts people who play Aug main toons (who are grouped and stay close to their group).<br>
<br>
 <p>Cheers,<BR>
<BR>
Steppin Razor, BORS/Mid [Lvl 44 5-spec SB (mostly good at all, master of none)]<BR>
{Appeal to all Infs out there to drop their Buffbot handjobs... you don't need it, not by a mile}
<BR>
http://www.geocities.com/nage42/Steppin_Razor.html</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunraven01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SunRaven01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 5:26:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3766.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A fair change to balance out buff bots.</span><hr size=1> You guys act like assassins are the only ones who move away from groups.<br>
<br>
Maybe Bedevere is just a weird server, but bards are pretty damn mobile characters.  It's not uncommon for us to hang out at the MG while the bard goes to check out Supply or Crim, MG2.<br>
<br>
Concentration-based buffs were meant to get away from the &quot;have to buff every ten minutes problem&quot; that some other games had.  Look at how many people said they hated the idea of self-buffs because they didn't want to deal with recasts.<br>
<br>
You're also assuming that the only people who get buffed are those in the buffer's group.  This also isn't always the case.  Lots of times a person -- a mage, a tank, another stealther -- has come up to me and asked for a buff because his group didn't have enough to go around.  Now he has to keep track of I am for the next ten minutes?  That's not fun for anyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 7:15:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3766.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A fair change to balance out buff bots.</span><hr size=1> Another 'Nerf buff classes' thread.  Funny if you wern't serious.<br>
<br>
The resist buffs are not 'chant type' which go away if your distant from the group.  They are group buffs with 10 minute duration - you loose them because your away from the group when its recast.<br>
<br>
Assassins are not the only people to use buff bots, the buff bot 'problem' only effects soloists.<br>
<br>
Totaly agree with Sunraven lots of classes go away from the group for lots of reasons (some of them are buff classes) and constantly responding to demands for rebuffing is not fun.<br>
<br>
To deal with the problems of this particular 'fix':<br>
<br>
1) Cleric gets asked to rez some people who were exping while the main force is at the MG or assaulting a keep [looser].<br>
2) Power-guild stations a buff class in key frontier forts [winner].<br>
3) Assassin &amp; archer asked to camp corpses at MG1 while group goes to fight enemy at MG2 [looser].<br>
<br>
